PEP20 <i>sound</i> amazing, but then when this only way end up being way too verbose/ugly, you are kind of stuck with it. Compare:<p><pre><code>    #python
    import re
    m = re.search(&#x27;(a.+)(d.+)&#x27;, &#x27;abcdef&#x27;)
    if m:
      print(f&quot;{m.group(1)},{m.group(2)}&quot;)

    #perl
    if(&#x27;abcdef&#x27; =~ /(a.+)(d.+)/){
      print &quot;$1,$2&quot;;
    }</code></pre>
